                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report of the Deputies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council heard and approved the Report of the Deputies.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Approval of the Minutes of the Previous
                        Meetings</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council approved the Minutes of the 23rd, 24th, 25th and 26th Meetings.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Italo-Yugoslav Frontier and Trieste</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council reached agreement on the U.S. Delegation (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 186)<note n="38" xml:id="d236fn38">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_752">p. 752</ref>.</note> with
                    the following amendments: <list>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>The words “free State of Trieste” are replaced by the words “free
                            territory of Trieste”;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>At the end of paragraph 3, after the words “… Conference of Twenty-one
                            Nations” the words “in accordance with the procedure adopted at the
                            Moscow Conference” shall be added.</item>
                        <pb facs="0776" n="752" xml:id="pg_752"/>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Paragraph 3, thus amended, shall become paragraph 5, and paragraph 5
                            shall become paragraph 3.</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                        <item>The wording of new paragraph 3 (former paragraph 5) shall come up for
                            further consideration.</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">e</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Paragraph 4 shall be amended as follows: “The permanent statute shall
                            be submitted to the approval of the Security Council, which will report
                            to the General Assembly of the United Nations, in accordance with
                            Article 15 of the United Nations Charter”.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Italian Colonies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council adopted the drafted Article proposed by the U.K. Delegation in
                    document <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 177,<note n="39" xml:id="d236fn39">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_713">p. 713</ref>.</note>
                    section A.</p>
                <p>Agreement in principle was reached on the draft declaration proposed by the U.K.
                    Delegation in the same document, Section B. The Council instructed the Colonial
                    Committee to draw up the final text of this Declaration.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">V. <hi rend="italic">Date of the Peace Conference</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council instructed the Deputies to examine how long it would take to complete
                    preparation of the Peace Treaties in the event of the Council of Foreign
                    Ministers completing its work during the next few days.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">VI. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council will hold its next meeting on Thursday, 4th July, at 5 p.m.</p>
